    "In the past few years, the cross-sectional and distributional ramifications of climate change have been debated.",
    "It has been argued that rising temperatures may only or largely affect impoverished countries that are heavily dependent on agriculture and have low capacity for response to climate change (Burke et al. 2015; Feng and Kao 2021; Kiley 2021; Kotz et al. 2022).",
    "In line with this argument, we split our sample into advanced and emerging countries to investigate the impact of climate risk on these distinct country groupings.",
    "The outcome for advanced and emerging economies depicted in Fig. 4 as Panel (iii), (iv), (v) and (vi).",
    "The Fig. 4 emphasizes that both advanced and emerging economies are more susceptible to global risk shocks, than to idiosyncratic climate shocks."
  ],
